      contents:
        "<p>Join our Global Cybersecurity Governance team which is responsible for providing a common Cybersecurity Regulatory Framework and Reporting across the Siemens business units worldwide.<br><br>We at Siemens are more than employees: We are actively helping to make people's lives a little better every day. Would you like to be a part of that? Then join us. We offer you a high level of practical relevance as well as an opportunity to individually contribute with your knowledge and your visions around the world. At Siemens CYS you'll be working in the heart of Siemens' corporate Cybersecurity team together with the best.<br><br>We make real what matters.<br><br>This position will be a key resource in the development of our Cybersecurity Data Monitoring, Analysis and Reporting Platform.<br><br>Essential functions include, but are not limited to:<br><br>\u2022   Specification and development of software products in the area of email/document management and collaborative platforms and service-oriented architectures. <br><br>\u2022   Development and customization of existing web applications developed with modern user interface technologies (such as Angular) <br><br>\u2022   Supporting the customization of systems developed with C, C++ and .NET, .NET Core (C#) <br><br>\u2022   Implementing systems in compliance with software development standards and programming and usability guidelines <br><br>\u2022   Continuous improvement of knowledge about applied technologies, frameworks and active positioning of knowledge in the company<br><br>Use your skills to move the world forward:<br><br>\u2022   You have a degree in computer science or IT-related studies or comparable training, or are a state-certified computer scientist in software technology or information technology assistant. <br><br>\u2022   You have several years of experience in developing with user interfaces using HTML5, CSS3, LESS, SAAS, JavaScript, jQuery, Angular or React or VueJS <br><br>\u2022   You have experience in creating responsive web layouts <br><br>\u2022   You have previous experience developing with C, C++, C#, ASP.NET and Microsoft Visual Studio <br><br>\u2022   You are familiar with database and storage systems such as relational databases like MS SQL Server or PostgreSQL <br><br>\u2022   You have knowledge in multi-threading, web services, microservices, RESTful API and Service Bus<br><br>\u2022   Familiarity with wireframes and tools like Figma is a plus<br><br>Diversity at Siemens is our source for creativity and innovation. Leveraging different types of talent, experience, and cultural backgrounds helps us to be more competitive and better prepared to successfully face our society's demand. Therefore, we value candidates who reflect the Diversity we are proud to have in our company.<br><br>#LI-HYBRID #LI-VVG<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Cybersecurity<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens S.A.<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Experienced Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time</p>",
