      contents:
        '<p><strong>If you really want to make a difference - make it with us</strong><br><br>As a world leader in developing and producing the most advanced engineering technologies, we improve lives and further human achievements worldwide, while also protecting the climate - all thanks to our employees. Working with us, you have the foundation to develop personally and professionally. We give you the chance to do something meaningful, that benefits society and human progress. We give you the chance to make a difference.<br><br><strong>Your new role - challenging and future oriented</strong><br><br>\u2022 Performing pre-defined technical tasks (e.g. basic commissioning of products and systems, integration of components to a system, basic engineering and maintenance jobs) onsite and remotely<br><br>\u2022 Testing products and removing found errors during the takeover of the products <br><br>\u2022 Supporting customers remotely and onsite by providing 2nd and 3rd level user support<br><br>\u2022 Coordinating and accomplishing defined service operations and resolving product issues for customer equipment<br><br>\u2022 Supporting in generating sales leads for the pre-defined service offers<br><br><strong>Your qualifications - solid and appropriate</strong><br><br>\u2022 Secondary school degree in Electrical Engineering <br><br>\u2022 At least 2 years of customer service experience in medium voltage or low voltage system is beneficial<br><br>\u2022 Computer literacy <br><br>\u2022 Knowledge of English, both written and verbal<br><br>\u2022 Strong customer focus<br><br>\u2022 Excellent communication skills<br><br><strong>We are looking forward to meeting you!</strong><br><br><b>Organization:</b> Smart Infrastructure<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens d.o.o. Beograd<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Mid-level Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time</p>',
