      contents:
        '<p>Challenging times require flexibility and adaptability. Therefore, Siemens Mobility Portugal has created a "New Normal Working Model". This gives you the flexibility to work from the safety of your own home while you can still count on full office support.<br><br>Siemens Mobility provides integrated Mobility solutions for urban, interurban and logistics for efficient transportation of passengers and goods. <br><br>With digitalization we enable Mobility operators worldwide to make trains and infrastructure intelligent. Our business unit Software creates and develops innovative high-quality software for trip and train planning, mobile ticketing and comprehensive Mobility as a Service (MaaS) solutions. Our apps have been downloaded more than 200 million times overall.<br><br>We share one common goal: enhancing the passenger experience with our combined power for the future of Mobility. <br><br>Siemens is operating a Software Development Center in Portugal targeting Intelligent Solutions for the future of Mobility. We want YOU to join our team in the capacity of:<br><br><strong>Senior Java Developer (m/f/d)</strong><br><br>In this job opportunity you will be able to work in an international project with the Siemens Mobility portfolio Company eos.uptrade, the market leader for Mobile Ticketing solutions in Germany.<br><br><strong>With us you don\'t just write code, you develop software. Here is what you will be doing:</strong><br><br><ul><li>Develop our new, innovative sales and ticketing product generation based on leading edge technologies like Java , RESTful APIs, Kafka, Kubernetes in a microservice platform </li><li>Work in international x-functional teams taking end-to-end responsibilities in requirements analysis, system design, development, integration and deployment;</li><li>Development, pair programming, code reviews and analysis;</li><li>Further development and optimization of our build and deployment tools with a focus on the highest possible level of automation;</li><li>You will closely work with our dynamic and agile teams from eos.uptrade in Germany. Occasional business travel to Hamburg (Germany) and/or other locations may be required.</li></ul><br><strong>Spaghetti belong into the kitchen, but never in your code. Your ingredientes for the job:</strong><br><br><ul><li>University degree in informatics, computer sciences or a similar degree;</li><li>Long-term experience in Java backend development;</li><li>In depth experience in Java, OOP, Java frameworks (preferably Spring Boot and/or Quarkus), SQL and GIT;</li><li>Team player with passion for quality and the ability to transform complex and manifold requirements into efficient, sustainable and modular software components;</li><li>Basic knowledge of containerization (Docker) and cloud-based hosting (e.g. AWS);</li><li>Advantageous is experience with Microservices, RESTful APIs, Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes, Kafka, PostgreSQL and/or Elasticsearch;</li><li>Fluent in written and spoken English is a must; German language is a plus.</li></ul><br>If this sounds interesting to you, please <strong>send us your CV in English</strong><br><br>#LI-PB1<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Siemens Mobility<br><br><b>Company:</b> SIEMENS MOBILITY, UNIPESSOAL LDA<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Experienced Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time</p>',
